The Department of Energy has released a report called Wind Vision: A New Era for Wind Power in the United States, which highlights the long-term benefits of investing in America's wind energy industry. The report states that wind power supports over 50,000 American jobs and supplies enough energy to power 16 million homes. The United States is currently the global leader in wind energy, ranking first in the world in wind power generation. The report shows that with technological advancements and cost reductions, wind power could economically provide 35% of the nation's electricity and supply renewable power in all 50 states by 2050. The wind energy industry could support over 600,000 jobs by 2050. The report also highlights the environmental benefits of wind power, including reducing carbon dioxide emissions and water consumption. Wind power is seen as a key component of the Obama Administration's approach to American energy.